reviewText:
I was a little hesitant of ordering this wig because of it's price. Overall, over $45 bucks (including shipping) for a Halloween wig is a bit much. Because I could not find anything better for my costume, I decided to stick with this one. I was very surprised when I got the product. The wig looked very natural and full. The color of it was just like the picture above. It did not come wrapped up in some tiny bag, so the hair was not tangled up at all (which was the issue that I used to have with some other wigs that I purchased previously). The wig presented itself very well. I got a lot of complements on it along with the questions of where I got it from. After the party, the wig is still in perfect condition. It should last you for more than only one wear. Definitely worth every penny!

PROS:
 - very natural
 - full
 - the color is exactly as pictured
 - great packaging
 - will last you longer than one wear

CONS:
 - price (it's a little expensive BUT it's definately worth every penny!)
 - visible wig-line (but you can easily fix it, if you spend some time on it)

But the second and biggest complaint I have is that darn flexible bottom section it has that i always hate on sweaters because it always rides up so easily, I knew this would be an issue too that's why I bought it one size bigger( I'm xl). Hardly worth the time, hassle or cost involved in returning to England so I will be donating them to one of my local shelters but will be removing the brand packaging that states "thermal" as I shudder to think they would be given to someone homeless who would genuinely need THERMAL socks during the cold Ohio winters. But ordering here, I found just what I needed and with 6 pair, I won't run out of clean socks and the price is very reasonable. I thought they might be a little heavier though. They're made from 90% Acrylic and 10% Polyester and are thicker than a plain cotton sock but not as thick as something like boot socks. They have a small rib knit. Still, they feel warm, maybe not "incredibly warm" as advertised but warm enough on a cold tile kitchen floor in the winter. They also feel soft. I don't know how sturdy they will be, but I'll post back here after a couple of months and let you know how they're holding up.

Online, the photos looked beautiful.  An amazing ring - very unique - very cool.  I haven't seen another like it.  I was impressed.

Normally I wouldn't buy jewelry, since I am a jewelry designer/maker myself, but this was just gorgeous.  The tsavorite garnet is so rarely used - and the idea of it set into the black rhodium was totally unique, I LOVED the hazy-looking green quartz cabochon...

Anyway, when it arrived I was disappointed.  The quartz was basically a very faint yellow - almost somewhat lacking in any color - and totally crystal-clear as far as clarity - not cloudy-looking at all, which is what I thought gave it such a unique look.  The tsavorite appeared to be glued-on and the diamonds may as well have not even been present.  They are so so so tiny that they're totally pointless.  They add nothing to it.

The quartz cab in the center is SO BULBOUS.  It sticks out so far - it's not oval and somewhat "flush" with the setting as it appears, no... it sticks WAY out and just looks ugly.

I had really high expectations for the ring and maybe that's why I am giving it such a harsh review.  Knowing as much as I do about jewelry, I will simply say it is wayyyy overpriced - but, I was willing to give it a whirl anyway because it appeared so beautiful on screen.

I took it out of the package, slid it on my finger, took it right off and packed it back up to be returned - all within less than 5 minutes.  :(

I got this watch as a graduation gift from some family friends and it took me a few hours to realize how great this watch actually looked and felt.  I find myself staring at it all the time in the mirror and even as I type this review.  I wasn't sure what to think of it at first when I got the box, seeing that it was a Seiko.  When I think of Seiko I think low cost, legit quality, nothing flashy, good for active lifestyles, but not too attractive.  When I opened the box I was pleasantly surprised by the size of the face, the unique way the colors and dials all blended together, and the weight/feel of the watch when I picked it up.  This is a solid watch with crisp, sharp hands.  I love the black middle section of the band and the white 5-minute increment markers.  You really have to see this watch in person because the picture doesn't do it justice.  This is probably one of the more expensive Seikos I've ever seen, even though I don't shop for watches much, and though I got it as a gift I think that the prices I see for it now are fitting for what you get.  Don't take my word for it, go to the store and look at it or check out better pictures on the Seiko website.  My only regret is that I feel bad for my Swiss Army watch I got for Christmas (I'll probably have to hide this one from my parents for awhile haha).

Positive highlights
- Great face size and thickness
- Masculine but elegant colors (black and white) with hints of chrome, red, and silver
- Black center wristband links to match the black face areas
- Great weight; not too heavy but feels like you've got something special on your wrist
- Kinetic Direct Drive, self-winding with a power meter that noticeably moves upon rapid arm movement (I thought this would be pointless but then I remembered my girlfriend's similar Eco-Drive Citizen watch that ran out of juice unexpectedly; the meter hasn't even come close to nearing empty yet); you can even wind/power it with the crown if it's ever completely dead
-You can set the day of the week as well as the date

Negative highlights
-No chronograph, which I was liking with my old watch for keeping track of grilling steaks and burgers but I guess it's not hard to remember what time I start something...
-Original price (I think I've seen it for as high as $1800 somewhere, a couple $1600, but the Seiko website has the MSRP at $1300 right now); regardless you can find this for around $700-$900 right now and I honestly think it is at the top of the ladder if you like Seikos or Japanese watches
-No precious metals or rocks, but who needs those really when it looks great without them?

Conclusion
-Unique, manly, elegant.  Subtle hints of flashiness.  Check this watch out and try it on yourself and I doubt you'll be able to say it is not a quality, attractive piece.  If you're looking for something you can wear day-to-day at work, running errands, or even going out for under $1500, even under $1000, look no further.

I was provided a set of Quality Stays Stainless Steel Carbon Fiber Style Cufflinks for review and was asked only to give my honest opinion, so this is what I found.

The set came in a small gift box that displayed them in the box with elastic bands holding them down.  Looking at the set, they look very nice.  The build is solid and the design is great.  The hinges are strong and stay in place very well.  The post has a slight curve to it so that it wraps around your arm, instead of sticking out.  The Carbon Fiber design insert was attached strongly and looked nice with clean seams.  They fit very well on my shirt sleeves and matched one of my suit coats perfectly.  Overall, this was a nice looking and well designed set of cufflinks.  If you are looking for a carbon fiber design in a pair of cufflinks, this set is worth consideration.

reviewText: I have purchased a half dozen of this exact type of sunglasses from different suppliers on Amazon over the last year. All of them have broken in exactly the same spot after a short period of time. They come from different brands with different names but they all break in the exact same spot. Some will last a month, others only last a week or two. Whoever made the plastic mold for the frames made a critical mistake when designing the frames because they fail from even the slightest pressure. Put them in your pocket, they break. Drop them on concrete, both sides will break. Look at them the wrong way, they will break. I have wasted so much money trying to find Oakley look-a-likes I might as well have just spent the money on real Oakley's. These are a huge waste of money, even at such a low price. The point of failure is on the top edge of the frame on the left and right sides of the nose bridge. Even if the glasses are just sitting on a table, they will eventually break because the frames have a weird elasticity to them that puts constant pressure on this weak point. It's a really strange engineering failure, and a real shame because they look great. I have $5 chinese wayfarers from Amazon that have been crushed repeatedly but never break, unfortunately this particular style is just no good. Don't buy this style unless the frames are noticeably different, they all come out of the same mold in a Chinese factory somewhere and they will break immediately!
summary: They always break in the exact same spot, waste of money

For the price, it's hard to find a better pair of sunglasses.  I actually went back and bought another pair for my son, because I liked them and he liked the way they look.  I know a lot of people get hung up on particular brand names, which I've always thought it nonsense.  No, these aren't Oakley or whatnot, but you're also not paying a premium just to have some brand label on your glasses.  They're comfortable, functional, and stylish.

I tend to prefer glasses that don't have nose pieces on them, since not only do they bend and misshape the glasses eventually, but they're nowhere near as comfortable.  These glasses are quite comfortable.  They do have a bit of a "hipster" look, but overall they're a pretty standard style.  The lenses are pretty large, which is actually good since the sun can come at your eyes from all directions.  Since my wife works in ophthalmology (doing eye surgeries) I hear a lot of terrible stories about the various damage done to people's eye either in accidents or by not taking care of them over time.  So having good coverage on my eyes was important.

I can't really judge just how much UV light these things block, since I don't have the testing equipment and humans can't really see light in that spectrum.  But what I DO know is that it dims things just enough that you're not squinting, but it doesn't darken your environment.  I'm guessing these might also block some of that "blue light" people complain about with things like monitors screens.  I only say that because it does make cell phone screens look a little dimmer.  So, if you're walking around outside with your smartphone, you're going to want to turn the brightness all the way up (if you don't already).

In short: cool looking glasses that work for you whether you're a teenager, or a parent in your 30's... hahaha
summary: Comfortable, stylish glasses at an excellent price!

The blue light turns on and stays on while winding, this is so you don't remove the watch while the winder is on. The instruction manual says removing a watch while winding may damage the motor. I don't keep this winder near my bed at night, so I've never noticed the noise. Overall, it looks good, and I like it.

I have this winder, badged Designhuette, after years of trying others, and am in total disagreement with the other two reviews. I suspect another agenda here.  Don't be discouraged from a good purchase!  This watchwinder will satisfy all but the most devoted moaners(I only have 40 years of experience of automatic watches, from Chinese movements of all qualities and via many of the ETA/Valjoux/Sellita models of movement through to Breitling/Rolex/Omega and peers, so maybe I don't know what I am saying.  I'm pretty sure I do...

Whoever designed and developed this watch winder has no knowledge of automatic watch perception. If you ask any watch maker or watch repair professional what is the effect of magnet on an automatic watch, they will tell you do not bring your automatic watch close to a magnet ever if possible, and yet this watch winder has magnets just inch and a half away from the watch, the glass door has magnets to hold the door closed. The idea of powering multiple units just by placing winders next to each other is nice, (only up to 4 units), but power consumption of the winder is 5 times more than any other watch winder since it uses 12V AC adapter and keeps broadcasting power even if the units are not in rotating mode, (this technology is new and its effect on human health is not known yet). Motor is not quite enough, if you place the unit on your night stand next to your bed it will keep you awake, the size is very compact which is a plus. The case quality is not good very thin and cheap plastic. I returned this unit back to Amazon for refund, and bought another winder which is 10 times better for just $30.00 more.Single Watch Winder Mahogany Wood w/LCD Dispaly Do yourself a favor and shop for something else.
summary: This Versa brand watch winder is the worst watch winders ever.

If you're looking for a good outdoor piece of running gear to keep you warm, wick
away sweat, and provide flexibility for temperature changes, look no further, I haven't
been able to find anything better.  Very well made.

You've got the hood option (or not), the roll out mittens option (though they don't have a
thumb cover, too bad), zipper in front opens wide and far down, if you're really warm, etc.
Weirdest feature is a big, long zipper pocket on the *back* of the jacket, down near
the butt --- tough to get to...is it supposed to be for gel packs, running gear, etc., as almost
a pseudo-fanny pack?  Maybe.  I wish it was on the front -- so for that, plus lack of thumbs on the
mitten, I take off a star.

But overall, really good:  I just used it for the first time this weekend, in windy, COLD,
Northeast early AM of like 18 degrees (windchill was probably down to 10). I had one thin
long sleeve wicking layer underneath, and once running, this kept me nicely warm, but not
too warm.  If it had been colder outside, though, I don't think it would have stood up to
any more cold --- and if I wasn't running, I'm sure I would have been cold too.  But it's
a midlayer, so you can't expect that.  It wicked away the sweat very nicely.

****FINAL NOTE -- as the other reviewer noted, this is definitely FITTED (probably good if you want it
to wick away sweat, and not be baggy, etc).  I am 185 and 5'11, and I got the "L" size, and it's kind
of a "tweener" for me...It's definitely on the tighter side, and snug on the armpits (which are nicely vented with mesh, btw), but I have a wide chest and biggish arms.  But it's good length-wise.
I think the XL would have probably been too big.

Overall, I give it an A/A-.
summary: Overall excellent - but why the zipper pocket on the BACK?

I ordered this for a Jessica Rabbit costume. I was hesitant because of the price but went for it over the other red dress options because I figured,  for $90, it might be more like a regular red dress than some cheap looking costume item purchased at a Halloween outlet store. The material is less than mediocre and because it is so cheap and so "slinky" it was ridiculously difficult to alter on my own and I had to pay someone else to do it. The slit is in an unflattering location for most all body types and is not designed well. The cup sizes are way too small in comparison to the length and size of the rest of the dress. (Why can't skinny girls have big, natural (or not) boobs! No one ever gets those proportions correct! The top of the chest area is MUCH "pointerier" than shown in photo and the small amount of piping used to try and create a bodust-style appearance but the only thing it does is make it very difficult to alter .. For some strange reason technology regarding face warmers passed me by. As I was getting ready for Christmas, I did an Amazon search for 'face warmers', thinking I would get one of those knit caps we used to have as children, you know the ones that always ended up soaked with fluid from your cold nose and mouth?  The search took me to the next generation of face protectors, those made out of Neoprene. They were cheap enough that I bought some for the whole family. My thought was they would probably be alright for cool days, but since they were so cheap, they wouldn't hold up for the harsher Northern Illinois/Wisconsin winters. The designs available were amazing, from plain black to cool abstract designs.
On Christmas morning everyone was pleased with the items because they looked so cool. However, when they wore them outside, the real surprise happened! These things WORK. They actually keep your face warm. Now, it was 15 degrees, which is warm for winter up here, but there was no indication that these things could not handle lower temps. Not only do they work, they are extremely light and comfortable. My wife is a bit claustrophobic, yet the mask did not bother her at all. The eye holes even allow you to wear glasses! The covered mouth piece has enough holes to make breathing easy, but does not expose you to the cold. I can only say that I am now happy to 'discover' these items, and I will be extolling their virtues to all other Winter Workers!

I have been looking for a nice Bible cover for a while .  I actually purchased a few  between $20 and $35 , but returned them all because of quality in the make , the size or problems with the color .  Or ones that CLAIMED to be genuine leather , that were more pleather .  Finally I stumbled on this type .  I will have to say that the make and quality of the materials is " A+"  !! The reason it didn't make a 5 STAR review in my book , is because of the faded color and some design flaws .  Here is my list of +  and  -  for this item :

 PRO'S
+  The edges are reinforced , the form a book shape , once you add a book to the cover .

+  The cover is actually quilted and good quality .

+  There are SEVERAL pockets , that almost convert this in to a book cover / organizer .

+  Nice , large , functional , outside pocket .

 CON's
-  The color that I saw in the description seemed  MUCH brighter than the muted faded color I received .  I will try to add a picture , and you can decide for yourself  .

-  The shipping was extremely SLOW .  I DID get the super saver ; but I ALWAYS choose that option and this was the SLOWEST order I have ever gotten . When I emailed to figure out were it was at , they had a very nice "get over it ! " attitude .

 -  It comes with a built in " book mark "  .  I found it to be pointless .  They chose to make it out of cloth instead of the ribbon you would normally find .  So its big , bulky and not functional .

-  Because of the faded look , I have purchased another brand ( Vera Bradly) and the color quality on my new ( not as many pockets , though ) "GOOD BOOK COVER" is OUTSTANDING !!

The front left side off the wig was stuck to the tape used to close the bag it was in, which made that part of the wig frizzy and tangled. The only other negative is that top of he wig towards the front you can see the cap part. Other than that the wig was great. It was as bright in person as it was in the picture. I feel that the length was a tad shorter than shown but my wig also looks a bit curlier than in the picture. The part of the wig that didn't get taped was great. I wore it to work(I'm a bartender) and it stayed on my head great. It did fit a little snug which was great for me since I move and bend over a lot for work. QUESTION: Did seller planettools really try to pass off an oxidized piece of jewelry as authentic Chamilia TWICE for $50? Its one item in a bag - no quality control?
ANSWER: This appears to be a straight-up business con known as bait and switch.
FACTS:
1. What I received is NOT an authentic Chamilia box-clasp bracelet as shown. What I did receive is at best a silver-color bracelet with a lobster-claw clasp.
2. Chamilia does make a lobster-claw clasp bracelet, but it is stamped with logo and 925, indicating verification of silver metal content.
3. To make things worse, the silver COLOR on the lobster clasp bracelet I received is heavily oxidized (see photos below) showing the base metal, therefore DEF NOT 925 sterling silver.
4. In addition: The ferrules on both ends of the bracelet do not match authentic Chamilia bracelets I already own.
5. As an avid Chamilia collector, I have serious doubt that this is in fact a Chamilia piece at all.
6. A previous buyer noted the problem and I posted a question. A second buyer replied saying she received the item shown. So my choice was my mistake. It won't happen again.
DONT BE FOOLED!!!

I use Polysorbate 80 in making my facial cleansing oil.  It helps thin out the consistency as well as making it easier to wash off.  I must also say that the company that supplies this, MakingCosmetics has the best shipping possible.  They package securely and shipments arrive before the scheduled date.

Overview(active tab)

Safety

Resources

Polysorbate ingredients (Polysorbate 21, Polysorbate 40, Polysorbate 60, Polysorbate 61, Polysorbate 65, Polysorbate 65, Polysorbate 80, Polysorbate 81, Polysorbate 85) are a series of general purpose hydrophilic, nonionic surfactants. The Polysorbates are used in a variety of products including skin fresheners, skin care products, skin cleansing products, makeup bases and foundations, shampoos, permanent waves and fragrance powders.

Why is it used in cosmetics and personal care products?

The Polysorbate ingredients help other ingredients to dissolve in a solvent in which they would not normally dissolve. They also help to form emulsions by reducing the surface tension of the substances to be emulsified.

Scientific Facts:

Polysorbates are surfactants that are produced by reacting the polyol, sorbitol, with ethylene oxide. The number in the name of the Polysorbate indicates the average number of moles of ethylene oxide that has been reacted per mole of sorbitol. The polyoxyethylenated sorbitan is then reacted with fatty acids obtained from vegetable fats and oils such as lauric acid, palmitic acid, stearic acid and oleic acid. Polysorbates function to disperse oil in water as opposed to water in oil

reviewText: I am normally a loyal Stride Rite purchaser when my children are taking their first steps, but my 17 month old was taking off his velcro closure shoes very quickly at inopportune times, so I went to buy a new pair of lace-up Stride Rite shoes, but they only had ONE pair of new walker lace-up shoes and they're plain pure white. I asked in person at the store about discontinued shoes, and looked around online, but the only thing available was that one pair of shoes. My very active child would have those scuffed and brown very quickly, and they don't look at all like big brother's or mommy's regular tennis shoes, so I started searching around for something that would be a good flexible pair of shoes while he's learning balance and stride. I saw a few different brands that were well-recommended, but they all seemed to be velcro only. I saw the Preschoolians here on Amazon, and thought I would try them out. They came a few days ago, and they work great! They came with three different insole inserts in wide, medium, and narrow. The medium and narrow looked about the same width, so I left the medium they came with in the shoes even though my child has pretty narrow feet. So far, they've been working well. The soles are very flexible and bendy. The front of the sole is clear and has a "right fit" window so you can take out the insole and see where your child's toes are in the shoes. I laced him into his shoes the other day and after quite a bit of trying, he managed to get one off about 15 minutes into a car ride (typically he gets both shoes and socks off within a 5 minute car ride). I retied it a little tighter when we got where we were going. After about 2 hours of shopping, he had gotten the other off (again, this usually happens much more quickly). I retied it a little tighter and we headed back home. On the half hour car ride, he tried several times, but did not get the shoes off again. He seemed to have no problems walking in them, though they're a bit big since they're equivalent to a 6.5 because of European sizing and he just outgrew his US sized 5.5 shoes.
summary: Good flexible shoe for a new walker

What Is It?

Polysorbate 20 and the other Polysorbate ingredients (Polysorbate 21, Polysorbate 40, Polysorbate 60, Polysorbate 61, Polysorbate 65, Polysorbate 65, Polysorbate 80, Polysorbate 81, Polysorbate 85) are a series of general purpose hydrophilic, nonionic surfactants. The Polysorbates are used in a variety of products including skin fresheners, skin care products, skin cleansing products, makeup bases and foundations, shampoos, permanent waves and fragrance powders.

Why is it used in cosmetics and personal care products?

The Polysorbate ingredients help other ingredients to dissolve in a solvent in which they would not normally dissolve. They also help to form emulsions by reducing the surface tension of the substances to be emulsified.

Scientific Facts: $

Polysorbates are surfactants that are produced by reacting the polyol, sorbitol, with ethylene oxide. The number in the name of the Polysorbate indicates the average number of moles of ethylene oxide that has been reacted per mole of sorbitol. The polyoxyethylenated sorbitan is then reacted with fatty acids obtained from vegetable fats and oils such as lauric acid, palmitic acid, stearic acid and oleic acid. Polysorbates function to disperse oil in water as opposed to water in oil

I ordered this shirt for my wife for Christmas. Since it is advertised on Amazon as a women's shirt, I ordered the XL size (which should be equivalent to men's Medium). When she opened it up and unfolded it we realized immediately that we had received a men's XL. This is not a "sizes vary by manufacturer" situation, the shirt is significantly larger than any of my own men's Large shirts and enormous compared to my wife's other XL shirts. I called the seller, Poster Revolution, and they informed me that they only make this shirt for men, in men's sizes. The "women's" descriptor was mistakenly added by Amazon. The Poster Revolution rep was helpful, and offered to get me a full refund on a return, however I would have to pay for the return shipping myself. reviewText: Okay.
I love these sunglasses!

Rather disappointing. They're nicely priced, virtually cost zip... but besides the point. There's always glasses out there that are dirt cheap & can actually be fantastic. Anyhow, I'm a typical Sunglasses "nut". As of now, I currently have about a dozen to a dozen & a 1/2 pairs. Ranging from 3 pairs in particular RayBan/MauiJ./Smith & then I've about 4 or 5, ... $18-$35 pairs. And a few scattered about, that are anywhere from 7.99- $15, a few I own are the "as seen on tv"- HD Vision sunglasses. Regular unisex square/rectangular shaped lenses, & they're what got me obsessed w/ HD/Brown &/or Gradient Brown lenses. Literally the 3 that I have are all the same. One pair I caused the inner part of the lenses to become all distorted & slightly ruined but still usable, do to me over using lens spray cleaner (I now only literally only use lukewarm water and a tiny bit of mild soap, just as they always recommend!). But I then went back to rite aid and grabbed 2 more pairs-@9.99 plus I get 20% off most stuff there, @7.99 ya can't go wrong. I started wearing those around the house day & night, I mean call me crazy, but I was/still am in love w/ how crystal clear, crisp, clean & vibrant these things are, my eyes are sensitive to lights all the time, so to explain the indoor wearing, & the gradient brown color are almost perfect due to not being that dark, hence comfortably wearing them all day, in/out, so finally, what I'm getting at is one night watching tv, & having a year old 1080p HD w/all bells/whistles, I'm used to a beautiful picture to begin with, so at one moment, I needed to go use the restroom, así got up I took off the glasses to rub my eyes, then a quick glance at the tv WithOut glasses on, I realized WOW, the pic looked a bit crappier, then I put the glasses back on for a sec, & to my great surprise, they make an already great tv picture That-Much-Greater. Oh & btw, they're really decent sunglasses as well. Now sorry for my babbling, back to these X-loops, they're almost, pretty much the same, or fairly close however they're just a shade enough darker, that make me not able to wear them as long indoors, & 1 last thing, this is a bummer, but they are honestly not very clear, and "free of distortion", I'm talking, through zero fault of the owner, they like many others out there are just I suppose not made very well, when you've a clean lens and the view has a few kinks in it. These were my SECOND try at owning (X-Loops). oh well. It's not the end of the world. But my advice- buy another brand of HD

reviewText: Very soft and comfortable.  Takes a while for it to be delivered but worth the wait.  This is the second one I purchased.  I wish they had more colors to choose from because I love the material.

DKNY is my absolute favorite brand in clothing.  My first purchase with this company came in the way of perfume, Cashmere Mist. I thoroughly enjoy comfort. These long sleeve PJ tops are soft and fit extremely well.  I wear a 36DD bra and purchased a size large.  My first order of DKNY lounge wear was approximately ten years ago, so I've got experience with these PJ tops. The original price was $48.00, now $14.99 and I must say that's a reason for celebration. The tops aren't tight on me, nor overly loose. One thing to pay a lot of attention to is the way you launder this loungewear. I actually learned the hard way that it's a must to always follow directions and then some. You need to turn them inside out so you won't get pills on them. Wash in cold water on delicate and dry on delicate. I've found that air drying leaves a lot of wrinkles.  I use baby laundry detergent and liquid fabric softener.  Also, add a laundry enhancer for the pleasure of freshness. Don't hang on hangers, fold over the hanger to avoid humps on the top. I've worn these tops with jeans. Just add a lovely scarf and you have a new addition to your wardrobe. Highly recommend DKNY...

I ordered this watchband directly from Clockwork Synergy. On the plus side, the black, silver gray and red colors of the band are exactly what I wanted, as are the buckle and keepers. Other NATO bands I've tried felt thin and cheap. I definitely like the feel of a heavier band. It looks great on my Citizen BM8180-03E Eco-Drive watch.

On the negative side, this is a NATO watchband modified to to be a Zulu. It does not have the second piece of strap that defines a NATO strap. This part has been cut off and heat sealed. I might not have minded the fact that I was actually getting a Zulu strap instead of a NATO if the heat sealing of the severed part of the strap hadn't been so poorly done. I'd only worn the strap a few hours before I felt the irritation from the ends of exposed threads.

Fortunately, I'd read that this problem could be fixed by using an emery board to smooth down the rough spots. Since applying this solution, the irritation has disappeared. However, I'm left wondering how often I'll have to keep filing down the thread ends and how this procedure might affect the long-term wear of the watch band.

I don't really understand why Clockwork Synergy turned what had been a NATO band into a Zulu band, but continues to advertise it as a NATO band. If you buy this watchband, know what you're actually getting and be prepared to do a little work to make it comfortable to wear.
summary: A Zulu masquerading as a NATO

reviewText: Good value,teflon

This design requires you to fold the extra strap material back under the two rings that are part of this design. As a result, this band sits useless in a closet now. It wouldn't be so bad except the proper bands cost half what this company is charging for this subpar band. Check out the Ritchie brand on Amazon. They come in 18mm, 20mm, and 22mm in lots of colors, and two bands of different colors will cost you $12 (as of this review). I've got a half dozen of them that I've been using for a year now and they are stellar.
It would have been helpful to know that replacement springbars are not included with the strap. For the price, it seems they might have been. Would have saved me the aggravation of another order!

reviewText:
I just got this product yesterday. I had it on me for the whole day after I got it. New to watches, first time introduced to straps and wearing one.

Overall thoughts:

- The band is fairly comfortable, took out my light titanium band on my watch and replaced it with this made it much lighter still. However, all is not perfect. The edges are somewhat abrasive, mildly scratching the inside of the lugs and poking my wrist a bit. I noticed an itchy, irritating sensation and upon inspecting, it was because of the stitching on the inside of the band. Wish something was applied to smooth over those areas, would make it look and feel better.

- The box it came in was nice and all, but I wish there was an option to just receive the strap without the fancy box and buy it at a lower price. Felt like I paid a bit more because of the box.

- The thickness of the band was just right, did fit snugly past the spring bar to my watch, thankfully.

It really is a nice-looking belt buckle and the price is excellent.

A couple caveats:

--If you're a person with Dunlaps Disease (where your stomach done laps ovah yo belt) you will find this buckle a tad painful when sitting, as the tips of the horseshoe stabs into your sorry gut. (Personally I've got six pack abs, so this was never, frankly, an issue for me. At all. Really.)

--Beware the belt hole for which this buckle is meant. I attached mine to a lovely hand-tooled leather belt, but the holes were fairly tight for the ball-and-post of this buckle. In fastening and unfastening, this baby would POP in or out of the holes. That is, I had to force it in and pry it out of the belt hole while fastening or unfastening. As a result, after about 4 months of use, the little ball on the buckle post popped off, rendering the buckle useless for me.

But I'll be doing some sit-ups and buying another one. It's a swell buckle.

reviewText:

SMS

The watch winder is exactyly what I wanted for my watch.  It does an excellent job and keeps the watch running and on time when I do not wear it.
I needed it because the watch is one that self winds by the movement of my wrist and I only wear it on weekends.

I ordered this watch winder because it had decent reviews and was on the low end of the price scale for winders. I haven't had it long but so far it is working fine and has kept my automatic watch wound. I'll update in a couple of months whether it's still working okay.

UPDATE;It's been almost two months since I purchased it and the watch winder is still working fine. It automatically winds for one hour and then rests for three hours and then winds for another hour and so on. It has a switch that can be turned on to rotate clockwise or switched to rotate counter-clockwise. It's also very quiet, which is nice. I've bought a couple of other automatics in the meantime and may order another one of these winders, or maybe a one that takes multiple watches.

UPDATE; It's now over a year and a half and I use it every day, so it's been on and working for a pretty good amount of time and it still works fine.

Arrived on time and the quality is as expected.  The unit has been spinning the watch for several days.  I'm interested in tracking its long term reliability.  Looks like a good price versus value item.

I purchased this watch from another company on Amazon for $8 and even at that price I still feel ripped off. That company no longer sells this watch. I suspect because of all the complaints. Before they stopped selling it, they offered to let me keep it for free if I would not publish a negative review about the watch and and their company. I can tell by the picture that this is the exact same watch from the same maker. As a service to other Amazon customers I am publishing this review wherever I see this watch sold.

 This watch is so cheap it is like a bad joke. The front crystal is plastic. When I tried to pull off the clear plastic sticker that was affixed to the watch to protect the plastic crystal, I pulled out the crystal with the sticker. The watch weighs almost nothing because the case is paper thin cast aluminum. The "bronze tone" on the watch is either the cheapest plating ever or paint. It is easily scratched down to the bare silver colored metal beneath with the slightest pressure. The cover does not open all the way and it does not snap closed when you try to close it. (You have to push the button to get it to close) The watch face is positioned wrong so that you have to hold it like a stopwatch to read it. (I got a different pocket-watch from China recently and it was the same way. Apparently the makers of these Chinese trash timepieces have never seen a real pocket-watch or don't care to make them like real pocket-watches. Lesson: Just don't buy pocket-watches made in China) The cheap quartz movement inside is the size of a dime and obviously made for a small woman's watch. The battery is microscopic and I've never seen one like it for sale in America. Bet it costs more than the watch to replace it. May as well mention, the watch was running on the battery when I got it, that means the battery has been running down since it was put in the watch. They didn't even put in a piece of removable plastic to preserve the battery life until the watch was started by the customer. This thing is like a child's toy. (That is if you want your child playing with something cheaply made in China that is probably covered in lead paint and will break in seconds) I can't say enough bad things about this watch because there is nothing good to say about it. I see this watch being sold for over $20 by some companies on Amazon. They should give it away for free as an apology for the insult of just thinking of taking your money for it. (The way the company I bought it from did) Save yourself the time, trouble and cost of shipping it back after you get it and see it is worthless. Just don't buy this watch at any price.

reviewText: I received this in August 2014 and used it daily until now, January 2015. It had to be replaced because it was literally coming apart at the seams, all of them. It was not overburdened with cards, either. Money was difficult to slide in and out as it tended to drag on the inner lining. Additionally, the leather was too smooth for me. It could be difficult to handle at times, and it doesn't 'grip' your pocket material at all. If not put in your pocket all the way, it could easily slip out. The design is terrific, but can be found in other brands, which I did, without the slippery texture leather. We'll see how long this one lasts. My first lasted about ten years, but did not have any identifying labels left on it when it was retired, so it was a guess in replacing it. They are not expensive, so I suppose you can't expect too much. However, due to the problems mentioned, I can't recommend it.

It was clear in the photo, so I assumed the stone would be clear. So, if you order the robot, you probably want to include your preference in color: Choice 1, 2, or 3. "Can't hurt; might help." reviewText: This ring is gorgeous in person and my husband loves it! The cubic zirconia stones look so real and the metal is shiny and beautiful. For the price you pay, you can't beat the quality. Ring looks authentic. Very satisfied couple!!

I ordered this ring to serve as my fiance wedding band for the wedding day since we had decided to scrap the big wedding and elope well before we planned. The ring I originally decided to get my fiance was a $2000 ring from zales that is almost identical to this one except their stones are real diamonds. Since we moved the wedding date up I would have been unable to complete the payments in time. I begin to search amazon and I found this ring. The ring is worth the money. It has the same high quality look for nearly next to nothing. I read other reviews and was a little concerned about the finish. Once the ring arrived I scratched it a few times with my nails and I saw how easily it marked, but those scratches were easily wiped away with a soft cloth. My husband's finger is a size 12.5, these rings run big! I actually had to go down by a full size and the 11.5 fit great. the ring is very light and he says it is extremely comfortable. The CZ that were set in the ring wasn't a very high quality CZ (you are not going to fool anyone who looks closely) but it still looks pretty nice. The only thing that was a slight disappointment for me but by far is no deal breaker was the color of the ring. The picture displayed had more of a darker grey with a blackish undertone. The ring that arrived was much lighter, it had a light grey , stainless steel type of color. That wasn't a big deal but amazon was selling other rings that looked similar that had that color for half as much I sent more money because I thought I was getting that particular color. Overall I am pleased with the purchase since it saved me $2000 and it arrived to my home promptly.

reviewText:
As one reviewer said about Tiger Eye Stones, the picture does not do the actual beads any justice.  The bracelet is a little small for my wrist. I'm a 6'4, 200lb male. My wrist measure about 7 1/4 ", by small I mean the bracelet still fits my wrist comfortably (the cord stretches) but traces of white cord were drastically visible between each bead. Also, some of the reviewers of similar bracelets mentioned how their bracelets fell apart after two or three days of use, with no strenuous activity.  I think they may have worn their bracelets in the shower.  From my personally experience many different types of stringed bracelets won't last long if worn in the shower, and like many people I don't care for taking my jewelry off before getting in the shower.
 Consequently, none of these complaints are an issue for me because I tackled the size issue and the falling-apart issue with one simple fix. I re-strung my beads upon receiving them in the mail. There are many different types of string that are used to string beads. Right now I testing out and researching what would yield the best strength and water resistance.  I combined the Tiger Eye Beads with beads from another bracelet in order to increase the length of my bracelet. In all, it took 22 beads to get the desired look and length I wanted.  I used 11 Tiger Beads and 11 beads from my other bracelet.  From my calculation there were only 17 beads on my original Tiger Bracelet.
I am extremely happy with this product. The 10mm beads are the perfect size...not too big, not too small. I really wish I had something to compare the size to but they are considerably smaller than the Wood Calligraphy Word Beads that I purchased( maybe half the sized). It took a little work to get the product right for me and delivery takes a few weeks but I knew that going in, so I give this bracelet 5 stars.
summary: Beautiful Beads...Bracelet May Require Some Work

reviewText:
So in my world, a 3 star rating isn't bad. It's ok, which is exactly what this watch is. The styling is fairly cool.

The watch doesn't buckle or adjust, so plan on the band being either loose or tight, unless you fit right into it's sweet spot. I don't. I purchased the large, and am a man of average build, and the watch is loose on me. I don't mind, though.

I'm a little disappointed that the band will have an empty cavity where the GO chip would have been.

Also of note, this watch touts an emergency phone number and reference code that first responders can use to access your vital information in case you are incapacitated. I tried to set this up following the directions included with the watch, but couldn't find the link. There is a "live chat" function on Rumba's site, so I thought I'd ask how to set the emergency info function up. I put in my question, waited over 7 minutes for a response, then gave up without getting one.

I'm wearing the watch as I write this, so that's something. I'm a designer and this watch is something different. If you're after a different looking watch, and are not interested in the features advertised, go for it.
summary: Rumba Not Offering GO chip Any More

reviewText:
I own 4 RumbaTime watches and 3 of them have the cashless payment system and the emergency identification option which I think is awesome. Once you receive your watch from Amazon.com, you go to the RumbaTime website and register your GO watch, set up your account by including your emergency contact(s), medical issues, blood type, medical/dental insurance info, etc.

You also set up your Vitaband prepaid visa account and add funds in the amount of $20-$500 so that when your card arrives, you activate it and insert it into the sleeve of your new GO watch and use it at most convenient stores & gas stations.

RumbaTime offers a 1 year warranty so if anything goes wrong, remove your visa card and send it directly to RumbaTime and they will either fix it or replace it.

Bottom line is you cant go wrong with the GO watch. It's multi-functional, convenient, sooooo cute and a great conversation piece.

I saw an ad for this watch in a travel magazine and thought, "Wow!  What a great idea," so I ordered one from Amazon.  First, I never was able to get the chip that was needed for the swipe and use feature, which is OK since I don't know of any places around here that use the feature (I don't drink coffee and rarely use convenience stores.)  And then, after less than a week the battery died in the watch!  I haven't bothered to go to a place to replace it.  Maybe I will later ...

I've never owned a more durable watch than this Rumba. On the go, very sturdy, almost like a rubber material for the band. The go part of the watch makes visits to places much much easier, especially when you don't have to bring any kind of wallet or CC's.

reviewText: I have bought about 4 pairs of these sunglasses. Not because they are falling apart but because I have gotten drunk and lost them all. This is why I think this pair/model is good for me. I am not the type of person to buy expensive sunglasses so these are perfect for me and my irresponsible ways. Pretty comfortable and don't seem too cheap. They are supposed to be polarized, but I don't believe that they actually are (maybe I just don't know what polarized glasses are supposed to look like when wearing these). Overall, great value if you are just wanting a basic pair of shades.

You can get much better quality for better prices at actual jewelry stores. They are an I3 which means on a scale of how many inclusions these diamons have (black specks in the diamond) they are the lowest. The only jewelry store that actually sells these low quality diamonds are fred meyers jewelry, all other stores like those owned by sterling jewelry can not go below than an I2. At an I3 those black specks are going to be noticable to the naked eye and look practically like salt and pepper at that point. Coming from a Diamontologist and Gemologist.
summary: You can get much better quality for better prices at actual jewelry stores

reviewText:
Where to begin...

Lets start with I bought one just like this from a large national jewelry retailer for somewhere in the neighborhood of about $450 back in 2007. I had 30 days to return it and I did just that. $450 just seemed like a ton of money to me at the time and still does for a mens ring. In addition to that I was loosing weight and these rings can NOT be resized. Once they are made that's what they are. Can you imagine having to replace a $450 ring that fell off your finger because it doesn't fit?

A few years later I was surfing Amazon and decided to look into mens wedding rings since I had lost a bunch of weight and my original band didn't fit any longer. After quite a bit of searching I found the "Concave Tungsten" ring. I couldn't beat the price and at the time I purchased it I think it was somewhere around $90. They have since come down in price.

I love the strength and luster of the tungsten, this very ring saved my hand from being smashed about a month ago. Had I been wearing traditional gold or white gold I certainly would have had a boogered up hand. I have tried other tungsten rings and have found that no other compares with this one in comfort. This ring is completely rounded. There is not a sharp edge on it. If I could get it in a dark color I would wear one on each hand.

As for the seller, I have yet to find a better seller anywhere. The first ring I ordered was 1 size too big. No questions asked, no hassles they worked with me to get it shipped back and they sent me a new one that fit just right. The ring size being wrong was not the sellers fault. It was mine as I thought I wore the larger size. Again this seller is great to deal with and was very helpful.

Amazon was awesome as always.
summary: Great Ring at a Great Price

Perhaps you have noticed that in the boutiques these head pieces are about twice this price. This is certainly worth a try to cut cost. I would say that this headband (that has aspects of a tiara) is worth considering) It is by no means cheap, but it has just as much (or more) crystal sparkle and rhinestone as similar headbands twice its price. This headband is well designed as a floral motif that is subtle rather than obtrusive. This would go well with a gown that is similarly understated yet well constructed. This headpiece holds it's own without competing. This has a slight peak, making it similar to a tiara. From the back some pieces were glued while some were not, none of this is visible from the front. This is about 3/4 inches wide at it's widest point, a little shy of its advertised width of one inch. My major criticism of this piece it that it is not as heavy duty as some that I have seen. The wire the crystals are mounted on could possible kink without the more substantial headband backing. reviewText:
I bought this ring because I always wanted a mystic fire stone, and I love it! The box that it came in was not impressive, but the ring itself is just gorgeous, especially for the price! I bought a size 9 because I have bigger hands, and although it was a bit too big it works great as a middle finger ring. It IS very dainty, so if you are more into big gaudy jewelry, this isn't the ring for you.

Color-
I find that under natural light it appears to be mostly dark purple with a hint of green. The side stones are very sparkly, and the band is extremely reflective. It is very eye catching, so I wouldn't recommend driving with your ring hand out the window (unless you want to blind other drivers).
In unnatural light, more attention is drawn to the center stone because more color is visible (in my experience). I have received many compliments at work.

Durability-
In the few days I have owned this ring, I have worked on cars, been in a hot tub, and done dishes. The stones are still intact and there doesn't appear to have any scratches on the band. The rhodium plating is wonderful over the silver, as it prevents tarnishing. So far nothing I have gotten my hands into have caused a chemical reaction with the rhodium. Also, it is a hypoallergenic noble metal, which is a plus.

Overall, don't hesitate to buy this ring because you will have wished you did!

As previous reviewers stated, the ring is smaller than expected, but still well worth the money. I have included a picture of it actually on my hand so that future buyers can see a size reference. For the reviewer who said that the stone looks gray, I am not sure what kind of lighting they have, but mine looks beautiful, with predominantly purples and greens. Good buy.

The picture makes the stone look like it is purple and green.  However, when we got the ring, it really just looked like a gray stone.  If you held it in the light and moved it, you could see shades of the purple and green, but just looking at it at a glance, it just looks like a gray center stone.  If the stone were more the colors of the picture, it would have been a beautiful ring.  Since I bought this for my 11 year old and she loves bright colors, sadly I am a bit disappointed in it.

My leather strap Type 8139 (Water resistant) has just arrived.
Delivery a bit longer than expected.
Initial appearance is quite good it does not look too flashy or "Chinese cheap".
The price was under USD10 but can't remember exact cost.
Dial is light-grey/white (with a crystaline appearance), case is dull black, back is stainless.
The strap is med brown & stiff; marked "genuine leather", I can't be sure if it is or not.
I have relatively small wrists & the strap was ideal in length for me, it would be too short for many larger wristed men.
To be honest I soon discovered that getting the strap on & off was a pain, my fault; I should have selected a different type of band.
Wife says it will loosen up & she knows these things.

I was disappointed to find the winding/time adjust crown somewhat loose - there is noticeable wiggle & this is avoidable so black mark there!
This probably indicates that it is not water resistant to any extent so I think I will need to remove just to wash hands - bugger!

I don't know the quality of the quartz movement but assume it's basic cheap Chinese so it should last a couple of years & if it does I will be happy.
My overall assessment of an as yet barely tested watch is; it looks fine, & it's different, probably will keep good time (not cronometer standard), & the strap will probably annoy me daily.
summary: Initial appearance is quite good it does not look too flashy or "Chinese cheap"

reviewText: After going several months without wearing earrings and having one of my holes begin to fill, I searched for some small earrings I could wear 24x7.  These were a little more expensive than some other possibilities I saw on Amazon, but they looked a little more legit, and I wanted to try these unique silicone backs.  And honestly I'm so glad I got these!  They're very light, and the size is just perfect: visible, but not too big.  They're definitely real gold, since my ears aren't itchy (even "hypoallergenic" jewelry irritates my skin).  The silicone backs are sooooo perfect; I can sleep in these earrings!  The only minor problems: the earring post is a little short compared to most other earrings I've used, and also it can take some finagling to get the rounded pushbacks attached, because I'm not used to the 'feel' and it's a little harder to position them by touch.  If you have manual dexterity issues, you might not be able to put them on yourself.  But otherwise, these earrings are a home run!

I have two piercings for each ear so I had purchased small hoops for the back and wanted something different for the front. I bought the 5mm size (I have 15mm but way too big and heavy) and they are PERFECT for the look I want - I have not had any problems with the backings - so far - I bought them so I could leave them in until I want to wear my expensive jewelry...I love them!! They are not too small and too large - if you are looking for a bigger ball - try a 7 or 8mm ball size. The prices are perfect and for this day and age, especially since gold is about $1200.00 per ounce (24k) and higher....
PAJ

The two tone appearance of this belt drew me in, and after showing up at my door in two days, exceeded my expectations.

Pros:
1) looks great - the two tone appearance looks great, allowing you to match your belt to a variety of shoes/pants/etc. The buckle looks just as good; the metal is heavy and has a mildly-aged appearance to it, which screams simple quality without looking gaudy.
2) durable - I've used the belt every day on two different size holes for the past few weeks, and it still looks like new. The leather is real, and it's strong, which means it won't break down for a while. The leather is admittedly thinner than previous belts I've used, but it doesn't appear to detract from its quality.
3) perfect size - I wear very small pants (size 28) so I've become very accustomed to incorrectly sized belts and pants, since size can vary through brands. The largest size hole on the belt is definitely a little bigger than a size 30 pant. I wear a size 28, and use the third (sometimes fourth) hole on the belt.
4) price - for $15, this is an unbeatable deal; especially for the quality. I plan on ordering another one soon, just to have after my current one inevitably starts to wear. (Also, prime shipping makes this an easy buy!)

Cons:
1) Can't think of any, I will update this review if something arises.

Overall impression:
buy, buy, buy!!!

This is an amazing wallet. I bought one of these directly from the seller in their shop in Amsterdam and promptly regretted it. It was expensive and seemed gimmicky, after all, I am not convinced that this RFID threat is a real or imagined one. The wallet is small, and I like to stuff mine with business receipts and money and stuff, so I figured it would probably be collecting dust in the inside of a month. The opposite is true. This thing is tricky. It throws five standard credit cards and/or ID cards in a perfect staggered method (read: easy to grab only the card you want).  I don't use more than five cards regularly, so that was enough for my goto cards. Then, this wallet is currently holding 15 bills, six additional cards in the inside pockets, as well as all of my receipts from my recent business trip (I'm sitting in the airport writing this now). This is as much as I really ever stuff in my wallet, but it still closes and clips, and fits comfortably in my front pocket with no different feel than any other day.  I LOVE this wallet so much that when I lost my original purple one (which fades to a very dark purple after use, so it is not too flashy), I bought another from this seller immediately, even though I have 6 new wallets in boxes with the money clips and card holders sitting on my dresser.  The product shipped quickly and came much faster than the seller predicted, like a couple of weeks faster.  This one is brown, works exactly the same, and was used for two days before the old wallet was returned. I really should give the new one as a gift to get someone else hooked, but I am so protective of my favorite wallet that I am hoarding it in case the new one goes AWOL again. The fact is, the leather is thick and quality, the build is excellent, the feel and look is professional, and the design is perfect...small and still super useable. I suggest you buy without hesitation, cuz you are not getting mine.

While Amazon's service was absolutely wonderful in regard to the absolute piece of garbage I received in a small white box (which was supposed to be a pearl necklace)--my money was refunded and the representative was very sympathetic to my personal situation regarding returning the item, I have to say--beware the seller of this necklace: because if they can sell something like this, and call it a pearl necklace of any kind, baroque, or any name for a pearl necklace at all, they can sell any sort of junk under any sort of name.

I was told, by the item description and by some of the reviews, that this was a good, baroque, pearl necklace. What I received was a loosely knotted string, with little shell pieces with no shape around sliding around on it (and I'm not talking merely baroque uniqueness--I'm talking flat pieces of shell with zero lustre). There was only about 36 inches of it, give or take a few mms, since I've measured it, and it was supposed to be all of 64 inches. It also was not even 7mm per flat piece of shell--I have a real pearl necklace that's 7mm per pearl, and this was more like six or five mm per piece of shell. So, on top of its being of execrable quality, it wasn't even as long or its "beads" as large as they should have been (upon closer examination--I wrote a hysterical email to Amazon about the quality of the thing, period, but I found upon looking at it and wondering if I could get away with giving it as a gift to an indiscriminating kid [my niece], that it's not even the 64 inches that it was supposed to have been, and it's not even 7mm per piece of shell; and I found that I didn't feel good about even giving this to a nine year old that has no "grown up" jewelry of her own, period).

Amazon has many, many wonderful sellers with wonderful products--for example, you can get a far, far better necklace (with actual, real pearls on it!), which even comes with earrings and a bracelet, for a mere 12.00 USD or so on this site; it won't be 64 or even 36 inches long, but it will at least be a pearl necklace, with decent lustre per pearl. Just search for "pearl sets." But anyone who recommends THIS necklace, that I'm reviewing now, has to work for the company that sells this merde, or be a family member of the owner or something like that; there's no other explanation why any sane person with any sense of class, even someone who knows nothing about pearl jewelry, would give this a good review.  I am very sorry if this sounds abrasive, and I hope I haven't overstepped any boundaries or rules set up by Amazon for reviews or for writing a review after receiving a refund--if I wasn't allowed to do the latter, please remove this review immediately, Amazon; and if I have overstepped any rules at all in this review, I am frightfully sorry and give Amazon full permission to just remove my review or edit it.

Amazon itself is a wonderful place to buy really wonderful deals--this is the very first time I've bought jewelry from Amazon and been even remotely disappointed; and I've bought quite a lot of jewelry from Amazon, for myself and for gifts, and it's always been great. All the sellers I dealt with, with the exception of this seller, were honest about what their products looked like and presented honest pictures of their products. This is the first time I've encountered this sort of horrible duplicity on the part of an Amazon seller, and, quite frankly, I was shocked.

But please, and I can't emphasize this enough, know you can count on Amazon to make it right, regardless of the issue. Amazon and its representatives are just wonderful places to buy from and deal with, respectively. I was treated with respect, kindness and fairness--and I didn't hesitate before buying from Amazon marketplace again, knowing that if the product turned out to be a dud, Amazon would make it right if the seller wouldn't or found some excuse not to do so.  Don't hesitate to trust Amazon itself, but really, beware this particular seller!

This one item is probably the most effective prop I have for our yearly Halloween display/decorating.  For the price nothing beats it.  The CD that it comes with is easily worth have the price of the item and can be used even without the box of course - very professionally done.  The box is a simple automatic dimmer device that responds to sound - either by the built in mic or a standard RCA type plug in.  The sensitivity of the box is easily dialed in with the big knob that you see pictured on the front.  This allows you to have only the loudest sounds picked up, like thunder claps or screams, to make it like a lightening effect, or the opposite which makes it perfect for a flickering light effect.  This flickering effect really makes it look like the power is coming in and out. I use one in this mode to make a lighted yard sign flicker like it is an old light about to go dead.  I am telling you that this will jazz up your party or scene so much everyone will want one. Just so you know, there are other "professional" lightening boxes out there that cost in the hundreds but this does essentially the same thing.  It seems reliable, has its own replaceable fuse, and is of solid construction.  I have had one running almost continuously for 3 weeks now and no problems.

Im very happy I went with this machine over a professional machine for 10x the money.  This product surpassed my expectations in performance and quality.  Just make sure you have plenty of extension cords and suitable lights for it!

reviewText:
My experience with this piece was a little less than spectacular.

The yolk-line neck won't fit anyone with wider shoulders. The cuffs on my shirt were wildly uneven, with one being more than an inch shorter than the other. The color is also extremely strange.

It lasted for the purpose I needed it for, however; though it needed some alterations.  I snipped straight down the V to widen the shoulders and added in some string to tie it.  Overall, it was durable.
Poorly constructed. The way the fabric was sewn to the yoke was incorrect causing it to pull to one side and almost impossible to even wear.

Fit/Width: Fits very well, however it is on the narrower side, so if you're wide footed, you might have to consider another shoe...or order these in a size up, otherwise they fit me pretty well (except my right foot is a little bigger than my left foot, so it's a little tight on my right cleat).

Upper material: The forefoot is made of natural leather (not Kangaroo leather like the Tiempo Flights & Legends).  The midfoot is made of synthetic leather.  To me, the quality of leather on the Mystics is very good for the price I got them for.  Though they do not stretch a lot like Kangaroo leather does, it still does the job very well, and it is also a very tough material, so striking the ball with these feel extremely comfortable.  The central lacing is a great feature.  Also, the tongue is not a fold-over tongue (like the tongue on the Copa Mundial), and it feels great!

Inside: No removable insoles, but the material that hugs the heel feels pretty nice and I didn't have any rubbing when playing in these for the first time.

Soleplate: Fantastic for artificial grass.  all the studs are round, so you turn easier on the surface.  The sole plate is not only really durable, its also really flexible & light...great innovation from Nike! These also aren't bad to play on hard ground or even firm ground.

Final Verdict: This a fantastic shoe for the price!  They start out at $80, but they drop down to around $60-70 so I would definitely consider buying these over any other Nike takedown shoe.  Not only they are durable, they are pretty light too, weighing under 10 oz! Nothing about this shoe feels clunky or bulky, its a quality shoe, not the best, but it is probably better than most soccer shoes being sold under $100.  You won't be disappointed buying this shoe, since it will last you over a season or even more!

FYI: Take extra care of leather soccer shoes because they tend to dry out (just apply some leather cream to the upper material a few times and you will be fine).

When they do wear out I get a hole in the toe or at the back above the heel, or on the ball of the foot, all the areas that are reinforced for long wear, which is why they last as long as they do, far longer than any other sock I have ever worn.

reviewText: At first when I took these pants out of the package I thought they would be too clingy and show every flaw, so I threw them in a pile of clothes and they sat there for a couple weeks. Finally I decided to at least try them on, and I am very glad I did! They are so comfortable, fit very well, and are not too hot for the miserable humid Texas summers!  They are perfect for work or a dinner out. They do have a very wide leg (palazzo style), but that suits my body type perfectly! The smooth wide elastic waist lies flat and doesn't roll, and they don't need ironing. This is one of those "happy accidents," as I never would have tried these on or ordered had I realized what the fabric was like. Now, I just want more colors!

These are insanely comfortable, almost like wearing dressy pajamas. They are also very flattering. They're great for the in-between seasons, when you just aren't sure what the weather may be. I will definitely buy another pair in the future.

I thought that these would be a good substitute for work pants, in the picture they look dressy.  When I received them, I was amazed at how LARGE they really were.  The band looks more elastic in real life than it does in the picture and it literally reached up to my chest.  They would be good comfy pants, but for anything  else, not happening.  I would order two sizes smaller than what you are and not plan on wearing them to anything except bed.  I gave these away to a larger friend and I was glad to see them leave.

I was extremely disappointed with the quality of the fabric of these pants in light of their price.  Additionally, they were way too long which leads me to believe that I was sent a 'tall' version.  I returned them and was refunded my money without incident.  Be sure to check the fine print when ordering from this vendor.

I ordered the Jet-Black pants from Jessica London - however, compared to my other black clothes, they look like glorified dark gray color, certainly not jet black, so that was a bit of a bummer, as it looks terrible when different shades of a neutral color are put together. Also, the size chart is a bit off - according to their sizing, I should have ordered a size 22/24, while I normally wear 14 or 16. Due to the huge difference, I ordered both pairs, and naturally I had to return the bigger pair, so my advise is to order down from the size on the chart. Otherwise, the cut and the material are very good, the pants look really good both with a blazer and with something more casual. Also, the shipping was very, very prompt. I would likely shop with this vendor again.

reviewText: Wow - I have been wondering for years why I don't see more bikini tops in bra sizes. I recently found Panache bras and got a correct bra fitting, and when I ran across Panache suits on amazon I was so excited! reviewText:
I think this is a wonderful product and a great value for the price. It was actually much better then I expected because of other reviews and low cost. I bought this mainly because I'm a Twilight fan and a collector so I don't plan to wear it but I think you definitely could with no problem. It's good quality and looks great and will hold two small pictures inside. If you're looking for a very high quality piece of jewelry this isn't it because it's not an expensive product but it is very worth the money for an inexpensive locket. I don't think most will be disappointed for any reason.

Update 11-18-16
I would like to add that since I purchased this locket I have also purchased three more for others in my family. Two for my nephews and one for my mom to have as keepsakes. Initially I purchased one for myself as a huge Twilight fan and I was highly impressed by the locket. My little sister passed away just over a year ago, yesterday would have been her birthday. She also loved Twilight and had a tattoo of the locket around her ankle. It is now engraved on her headstone. I gave each of her two sons a locket of their own last night when we visited at the cemetery to remind them of their mom and how much she loved them. When I see my mom she will be getting the fourth one I purchased for the same reason. I honestly don't understand the bad reviews because this locket is a gorgeous piece of jewelry and well worth the low cost. The three I've received so far have been very sturdy, beautiful and just what I expected and I have no doubt the other on the way will be too. Mine came in a gorgeous white bag and the other two came in gorgeous blue bags. My nephews are each wearing theirs and love them and they've so far held up to two young boys having, wearing, touching, opening and showing off. I would highly recommend this item to any lover of Twilight or just those who find it beautiful. I don't see how anyone could be disappointed. All of mine have been very well made, packaged and shipped. The writing has been very clear, the color exsqisite and the chain nice and sturdy. One of my favorite jewelry items!
One word "FLIMSY"
The locket was more beautiful than I thought it would be. It is very well made and something I will enjoy wearing for many years. Thank you for offering this to your customers.

I have macular degeneration and have to wear sun glasses.  My RX sunglasses needed to be changed but wanted to see if my eyes RX would change before investing the money.  I am not that old and refused to wear those big over the glasses sunglasses. I saw these in Cabella's that were for people who hunt and fish. The lenses really filter the light and when I put them on they actually looked stylish....perfect combination. I knew the frame I wanted and the lens color by trying on several in the store but they didn't have my size. Found them on Amazon at a great price and exactly what I wanted. There are different sizes and frame shapes so I would recommend going to a sporting store that carries them, see what fits best with the glasses you wear, then go on Amazon and order them. I asked my friends and husband to swear to tell me the truth, "do they look like those old people's glasses?"....they all said no, and I am pleased!!!
summary: Look  fashionable, filters the light & fits right over my glasses!!

I rely on shape wear to turn my shapes into sleek curves.  These definitely make my buns, hips, and thighs appear smoother and tighter.  However, they tend to create some unnecessary bulges around my midsection, which is relatively flat.  The wide waistband creates an indentation.  It also rolls if I don't carefully position it exactly on my natural waist.  That isn't to say these, or the waistband, are uncomfortable.  I prefer Assets because I find them very comfortable - they're light, breathable, and non-constricting.  The waistband keeps me from wearing these with fitted or a-line dressed, but they're just fine with belted dresses, slacks, and skirts.

I have been suffering with pain for years but I thought this was normal for everyone to have such pain after waking up and always blamed my mattress etc.  I was diagnosed with A.S. after an iritis flare when the opthamologist sent me to a rheumatologist.  After starting a biologic I searched the internet for other natural ways  to decrease inflammation.  Copper and magnetic bracelets kept showing up as helpful for arthritis.  Even though I was very skeptical of such items I thought I would give it a try.  So then I researched which brand was the best.  Bioflow comes up as a class 1 medical device in Europe so I chose this one because it is also made of copper.  I have also ordered some Sergio Lub magnetic copper bracelets which are very pretty.  So I wore this bracelet for a month but didn't think it was working.  I honestly could not tell a difference.  One day after a trip to Las Vegas my foot started to hurt a lot from all the walking. It hurt for 2 days and I could barely walk on it. I was showing the bracelet to a co-worker on the internet when I noticed I was wearing it upside down, so I turned it around.  The next day my foot no longer hurt.  It may have been coincidence.  So I continued to wear it this way for another month.  As the copper color does not match my jewelry that well, I took it off (still skeptical) and replaced it with a different magnetic bracelet that was silver in color (stainless steel).  Within 2 days I developed an A.S. back flare.  So I put the Duo back on and felt better the next day.  Could be another coincidence,(or the biologic working) but I'm hedging towards becoming a believer for using this item in conjunction with prescribed medication therapy.

I have no idea why this particular item couldn't be handled as quickly as most Amazon returns where after a couple clicks you can print out of return label.

I was concerned about ordering a replacement so close to our vacation departure but the Amazon Customer Service rep I spoke with said she'd send notification about the order to the "appropriate dept to ensure it was fulfilled correctly". It wasn't. They sent me size 0-6 months AGAIN. When I complained to Customer Service I got a lot of pat responses that sounded like they really didn't care that I was now out of time to order a hat for my daughter for our trip to Mexico tomorrow. I was very excited to get these gloves & had high hopes for them. I was very very very wrong!
I live in Southern New England & we had another storm hit overnight. This morning, 2/5/14, I went outside to shovel my 3 front steps & clear off 3 cars. I pulled out my new gloves for a test run. I was outside for less than a half hour. Not playing in the snow, which is what I had bought the gloves with the intention of using them for. Playing in the snow, sledding, etc. Today, I was just shoveling & using a car brush & dusting cars off. I felt my fingers getting cold my first car in. By the time I got inside my fingers were burning. I ran them under cold water to warm water to try to ease the temperature back into them. I swear I was on the verge of frostbite. I am not sure if the metal buds on the finger tips added to the cold & amplified it.  But these gloves do not keep any of the cold out. Very very disappointed in these gloves. They will be going back!

you have to be active, in and out of cold weather all day. Easy on, easy off and the Thinsulate makes them very warm. I have already washed them (after handling a muddy, snowy dog) and they look fantastic. I am partial to the 180s brand anyway, and have their ear muffs, etc. The cuff keeps every bit of snow away from my hands and is a good wind shield. If you live where you need a reliable, totally waterproof and durable easy-to-wear glove, then I high recommend these. (Oh, and the thumbs and forefingers have what I call "taps' so you can use your cell phone without removing a glove.)

I am sick to death of sunglasses. I have lost count of how many pairs I have owned. They always get broken, lost, scratched or a screw comes loose; but I need them, or at least I thought I did, because I play tennis and I'm a complete Jessie at playing when the sun is in my eyes. Call me slow or just plain stupid but it wasn't until watching Wimbledon this year that it dawned on me that hardly any of the professionals wear sunglasses but many of them, particularly the women, are wearing these visors. So I bought this to try one out and I doubt I'll ever look back. It's brilliant. It cuts the sun out enough to take it completely out of the equation and it avoids the sunglasses problem of slightly reduced visual contrast which always did make me spot the ball slightly later. (There's also the added bonus that it looks nice on too, so a winner all round).
PS Re: fitting, there is a good quality adjustable velcro strip across the back - worked fine for me.

It just happens when several layers of fabric meet so you have to have some help to zip it up. Again, no big deal.

I will be exchanging this size 8 for a size 10 but I do think the sizing is pretty accurate overall. If you are going to buy it, make sure you have time to size up or down via returns.
