reviewText:
This is what I call my 'Firkin', due to its undeniable similarity to the much more costly designer version by Hermes. Since I couldn't yet afford the real deal, this seemed like a wonderful alternative. Although I was a little hesitant in getting it as I wasn't familiar with the brand's standard of quality, I have been very happy with my purchase so far (bought it about a month ago) and get many compliments on the color (Cognac) and design.

The bag is roomy and can fit plenty of items, including letter-sized notebooks and folders without getting them bent. I like the sturdy base, as the bag doesn't sink down even if it is heavy and always remains well-supported. One thing that I wish I knew how to fix is that a few days after buying it, the bag began to flop over the front when I set it on the ground and no longer stands up straight. A minor quirk but I am worried that the leather might start to crease. The leather quality is good for its price, a little shiny but not noticeable. The straps are holding up well and I especially love the classy buckle lock detail.

For its price, this is certainly an elegant and well-crafted bag.

reviewText: Just received my belts, I ordered one in black and one in brown. Haven't worn either of them yet, but they look like good quality belts, good leather, really like the buckle, very nice. I like wide belts, no skinny little belts for me, and they just don't seem to be available anywhere. A comparable belt in a store is better than twice the price of these belts, and these are just as nice.

who needs a wide cinch belt

- that's not too wide
- that has no elastic, or tacky bows, fake leather, super shiny hardware or tassles
- and isn't so long that it has an end hanging down like a wee-wee
....

if you're looking for a simple leather belt with excellent craftsmanship, this is it. the pewter-toned buckle is understated, yet elegant. at about $16, it's great value.

i've looked and looked for a simple leather 2-inch wide leather belt and those at high-end women's stores usually are very long - around 38 inches - and cost at least three times as much.

Thirdly yes.. it has a worn out, chipped, faded looking off white color.. it says rustic in the description.. you can see it in the picture. Ordered matching set of bra, garter, and panty.  Shipped much quicker than was described.  Fits perfectly, but I had a strategy when selecting sizes:  I am a consistent 34C, ordered a 75D bra (because that was the enclosed sizing translation), but received a 75C, of which this error was to my advantage because it fits perfectly.  Though I am a dress or pant size 2-4 (or small), I have attained a couple extra inches around the waist in the last few years, so I ordered and received a M/38 garter, since there is no corset-type of cris-cross adjustment threading to tighten (nothing more unattractive than the sight of a garter that's too tight!).  It does fasten in back like a bra, with 3 rows of eyelet hooks as its adjustment feature.  My thinking was, "better to be a little too big than to be at all too small", and it fit perfectly too.  I ordered and received a S/36 thong panty, which also fits perfectly.  This feminine, attention-getting bra is a push-up bra, providing ultimate cleavage, with underwires and a shelf of removable push-up padding, which easily slides into their built-in pockets.  The straps are adjustable in length, and also adjustable for conversion into virtually any kind of outer-clothing style (bandeau, one-shoulder, halter, front-cross, back-cross, etc), or completely removable for a strapless bra all together.  It fastens in the back, with 3 rows of eyelet hooks for circumference adjustment.  The garter is the perfect element of balance to this ensemble, while daintily concealing any extra bulge one may have in their tummy.  But I warn you that only the sheerest of stockings will enable closure of the shallow plastic fasteners on the garter... any thigh-highs with a thick cuff will be impossible to fasten to the garter otherwise.  This non-lace, opaque material is buttery soft, and likewise, so is the sheer lace.  It is VERY comfortable to wear and soft on the skin, will not trigger itching, and is seemingly constructed quite well.  I have worn it once for a couple hours and could have worn it for much longer.  It truly does make you feel elegant and sexy, and I feel it would flatter any type of shape.  The color saturation is a couple shades darker/bolder than what was pictured using my monitor, however, but I assure you, this is still a classy ensemble and I can't wait to receive the matching grey stockings that I just ordered for it (a must!).  I have included pics of full details for each piece, since this was not provided in the ad.  For care to those of you who don't know:  as with all my lingerie sets AND per washing instructions of each piece, I will ONLY hand wash this set with only its own counterparts in cold water, with liquid laundry detergent for babies (Dreft), cold-water rinsing in highly diluted liquid fabric softener (do not pour straight onto the fabric... stir to equal consistency into your rinse water BEFORE adding the garments for rinsing), and pat dry between a folded bath towel (NEVER wring or twist)... as this is the ONLY way to maintain the initial shape, luster, and beauty of any lingerie article, while keeping the material snag-free and prolonging its lace to remain flawless and intact (and without clinging lint).  And please, at the VERY least, do not EVER put any lingerie garment in the dryer!  Very important if you want any type of lingerie to last and remain classy looking past its first wash.  I consider this purchase to be a great value and a great choice for anyone who loves the way they feel in intimate-wear.  My only complaint about this ensemble is that I don't quite look like the model does in it!  :)
summary: A Fantastic Purchase Choice... Will Buy Roza Alegra Again!

reviewText:
This is a nice bonnet, but it is best suited to a smaller head--did not fit well on a high school age girl.
The bonnet looks great, just runs more towards child-size.

Let me begin by saying this bonnet is cute, and old-fashioned, but it is NOT a pilgrim bonnet.  Pilgrims, and other colonial era fashions had much different bonnet styles, primarily ones that are softer fabric (not completely stiff), but are more floppy and cover more of the side of your head.  You can search this online for more information.

This bonnet IS perfect for the 1800's era, from Civil War to Dickens, and certain pioneer styles throughout the 1800's.  This bonnet is lightweight and a fantastic slate for decorating.  I have sewn on fabric to mine to match my Dicken's era dress.  I also replaced the strings with a wider satin ribbon, and added flowers and trim all around it.  I wouldn't recommend wearing it without decorating it, as the materials look too modern and lightweight to be historically accurate.
summary: Not a pilgrim bonnet, but a good base for bonnets from later eras

I found that a store-bought size 9 was just a teensy bit tight at certain times of day, on my "man hands" (large knuckles) so I ordered this ring in a 10.  (The stores only offer up to size 9; go figure.)  The 10 is loose now, during winter cold, however it may be fine during the hot, humid months.  I love how it looks on my hand, makes it looks a little daintier.

I have noticed other reviews expressing wishes for this to be offered in half sizes.  I will say there is at least one other vendor on Amazon that does, indeed, offer eternity bands in half and whole sizes, in different colors of stones.

The stainless steel material used in this ring was a clever idea and it looks great.

Update:  still liking my ring very much.  Don't wear it every day but when I do, I get compliments.  The other vendor's size information was inaccurate; they were selling the size 10 and calling it a 9 1/2.  And their ring was bent and the stones uneven sizes.

This might be the best travel item I've ever purchased.  It was expensive, but for what I paid I got a lifetime warranty on a 5.5-lb suitcase that is truly the cream of the crop when it comes to hardside luggage.

The pros:
- The inside of this bag has more straps and pockets than any other I've seen, allowing greater flexibility re: how much you want to put inside it without it all flying around
- The handle allows you to strap another bag on top of the suitcase (unlike the Rimowa Salsa Air)
- Did I mention the bag weighs 5.5 lbs?

The cons:
- The zipper may not be as sturdy as that on the Victorinox/Swiss Army or the Rimowa (the other 2 contenders), but so far it's held up fine and is covered under the lifetime warranty.
- The color of the bag allows it to get marked up easily, but most of the marks come off with the Magic Eraser (though I don't really care - I kind of like it looking well-traveled)

August 2013 follow-up: one of the wheels broke on my 4th trip using this bag: they stick out a lot more than the wheels on the Rimowa and Swiss Army, and one side of one wheel was missing after the bag got through customs. It was a hassle to push without the wheel, and it cost me over $40 to ship to Samsonite, even though the repair was free (and fast). I'm still happy with the bag, but wanted my review to have as much current information as possible.
summary: Ultra-Light, Lots of Pockets, Wheels May Break More Easily

reviewText:
I'm very happy with this bra.  I am 6 weeks post-surgery (breast reduction) and was having problems finding a bra that was light/soft enough, yet still had the coverage I needed up front.  The removable pads are great because you can position them according to where you need the nipple-coverage (or in my case, shield the sensitive tissue).

I found the fit to be spot-on.  Stretchy enough to get over your head with limited range of motion post-surgery... yet snug enough once you put it on.

Unlike a lot of the other stretchy/microfiber bras I've found, this one has straps that are more like a traditional bra and less like an athletic bra, so wearing it with t-shirts and wider neck dresses is easy.
summary: Post-Breast Reduction: Love it.  Very comfortable and gives me the coverage I need.

reviewText: It's always been a challenge for me to find bras that fit, so I was not very optimistic when I purchased this bra online. Well I went and got engaged....forgot about that whole getting a ring for myself thing. I tried on a few tungsten rings at the jewelry store where I bought my Fiance's ring. They priced around $200 to $299....I said thanks....but no thanks. So I came back to my long-time dependable friend...Amazon. This was one of the first rings I found and I thought it was just too good to be true. So naturally I bought it to check it out. This ring is just like everything I tried on in the jewelry store....pretty much identical. If anyone is looking for this style of Tungsten...do not get ripped off at a jewelry store. I am interested to see how the ring holds up over time...but as of right now I am very pleased with my purchase.

Quality - Good
Price - Excellent
Sizing - Excellent

I have read a few reviews about people saying that the ring was too large for them but I did not have this problem. I was sized as an 8.5 in a Jewelry store and that's exactly what I ordered here. Fits great.

If this is the kind of style you like...look no further in a wedding band than right here.
I bought this for my husband as a wedding band. It looks very nice, it's smooth, shiny, an strong. Its an amazing ring. It fits perfectly. An he loves the ring. Im very happy with it.

Before we brought this ring we had my husbands ring finger sized at the jewler but when we recieved the ring it was pretty snug so we contacted the seller and advised we would like to exchange it for a half size bigger. They sent us the shipping label right away and once they reiecved the ring back they shipped the new one that same day. Very nice and fast customer service. The ring itself is nice looking and so far so good on wear and tear. My husband works construction so he is harder on his ring.  Overall good service and product just think it runs about a half size smaller.

I think the width of the ring is perfect.  It will get noticed, because it's a black ring, but it won't scream "flashy" the way a 10MM ring will.  And no one will mistake it for duct tape, because of the shiny edges.  Personally, I usually don't like two tone jewelry, but you NEED the two tones or this will look like you wrapped your finger with tape.  I'm not sure I love the black versus simple silver hued metal rings I wore before, but it works.  I'm not sure I'd wear this on a Fortune 500 corporate office job, but if your office is fairly casual or you are in the trades, I think it works.  Just my opinion, based on what others have said or not said about the ring since I started wearing it.
summary: Very Light - Two Tone Important on Black Ring - Nice Quality

I'm a L/XL and ordered the 1X which wears true to an XL in a Woman's size.  At 5'4", the length hits me mid-calf. Delivery was fast and the item was well-packaged.  The fabric is smooth without any flaws and all of the stitching is quality - no stray threads to clip.

The outer shell is lightweight and it is lined with color-matched fleece which is removable via side zippers and snaps at the top.  The full front zipper has a snap placket, there are two snap chest pockets and two deep front pockets.  The drawstrings at the waist, hem, and hood all have toggles to cinch the strings closed.  The wrists have adjustable snaps and the hood, which is unlined, can be detached by five buttons.  All the buttons and snaps are color-coordinated.  There is also a vent with a snap mid-back.

This jacket is loose, allowing for movement and bulky sweaters.  Driving is part of my job and having a jacket which is not constraining while being light was my major consideration for purchasing this item.  I chose the Dark Pewter which is a dark gray with a steel blue tinge.

I highly recommend this jacket if you like your outerwear a bit on the long side.  The color selection is very good and I've been debating ordering a second... or even a third jacket.
summary: Finally... a real jacket for real women

reviewText:
to many people seem to be purchasing these Marathon "General Purpose" type watches with no clue as to what the actual intended type of use the military desired from this watch.
This is absolutely NOT a field rough service or weather proof watch. Thus the US military designation "General Purpose" as its designation. It was designed to be a disposable watch. The very first "e" design did not even have a removable back.
The only reason for these watches having a pretty high price tag is the choice to use Tritium tubes for the dial markers.
What is accurate unfortunately is from the first 1990 "E" design is that the tubes tend to come unglued from the dial face even when the watch is not abused. My 1990 model had the tubes file off the 12 and 9 position.
As far as Marathon's customer service I recently contacted them about replacement parts for my watch. I was instructed to contact the service department my email. I received a response with 24 hours informing me that they no longer had parts for my old watch.
As far as quality goes ask any serious diver about the quality of the JSAR and TSAR dive watches they produce for our military. They are often very prized possesions of hard core divers and our military.

These are terrible watches. It was disappointing when it arrived - they have a very cheap plastic feel, and they are lightly constructed. Worse, four months after I bought it, the tritium tube at 9 o'clock came unglued and was floating around freely inside the case. I'm an office worker, and the watch wasn't subjected to anything remotely strenuous. I e-mailed the company and it took them three weeks to respond. And, they wanted to charge me $50 plus shipping to "evaluate it" before they'd repair it. The watch was advertised as "guaranteed for two years," and having a "one year warranty" on their website. I'll never buy another watch from Marathon again, they're completely unwilling to stand behind their product and their "guarantee" and "warranty" are both plain lies.

I originally bought one of these to take the place of my Wenger Alpine when I was biking and doing other outdoorsy stuff.  I wanted something that was easy to read at night and that was lighter and with a smaller diameter.  So the marathon was perfect, for a while.
After about two months of use one of the tritium vials fell out and was bouncing around inside the watch.  I emailed Marathon but it was going to cost too much and be a big hassle to get it fixed.  I ended up taking the watch apart and gluing the vial back in myself.  All was fine for about another month when two more of the vials fell out.  Out of frustration I flew the Marathon straight into the garbage can.
The Wenger is still on my wrist a year later.

My canoe tipped over.  The watch was briefly submerged to a depth of 1-2 feet. I was not too concerned as the watch is supposed to be water resistant to 3 atmospheres, or 90 meters. Unfortunately, the watch stopped.  There was water under the crystal.  A battery change did not help.

I contacted Marathon Watch Company in Canada because I had only obtained the watch 9 months before. They simply refused to stand behind their product, saying there is no warranty. It seems that "water resistant" in this context does not mean that the watch can safely be submerged to any depth. Evidently the most the watch can handle is a passing rain or perhaps a light sweat.

It disappoints me that Marathon would advertise this watch as being the sort issued to the military. It certainly is not suitable for that purpose. After all, soldiers do get wet. The watch is accurate and easy to read, but for heaven's sake don't get it wet.

So I waited awhile before writing my review of this. I was skeptical when I purchased this, but just giving birth to my 5th child I figured what do I have to loose...other than $40 bucks.
Let me start by saying with each of my previous pregnancies it took me about 6  months to return to my pre-pregnancy size. I am not a large woman, I am 5'3" and weigh about 115 pounds and wear a size 3/5 pre-pregnancy.
Usually after delivering I have to wear the dreaded maternity clothes for a few months while my body is "returning to normal".
So after my last baby (baby # 5) I decided to give this a try. I AM GLAD I DID!
When I returned home from the hospital, I started wearing this from the time I woke up in the morning until I went to bed. By4-5 weeks post partum I was back into my pre-maternity pants! (My tummy is a different story) But this actually sped up my hips returning back to normal! That has NEVER happened this fast on my previous pregnancies! I highly recommend Shrinkx Hips to everyone!
Worked great and felt great too!

An unexpected C-Section meant this would not work for me.  I couldn't touch my stomach during the three weeks you can actually use these so by the time I could wrap something tightly around my hip area it was too late according to the fact that you need to use it right away while the hormones are still making things "flexible".  Nonetheless I gave it a shot but it was just too uncomfortable to wear - perhaps on a smaller person it would feel better.

I used this product after my first child.  Soon I was wearing my original jeans.  This belt was thin enough to wear under my jeans.  It is discrete and comfortable.  I would order this again and I plan to use it after my next child.  I'm giving a four because the elastic did bunch slightly after use but it did not stretch out.

To start, I should say that I received this product as a gift as a tester.  As far as sizing, I am a size 8/10 (usually "medium") and the XS/S size worked out fine for me.  (There is also a size M/L).

The hip belt felt a little awkward in its proper placement (1 inch below hip bone, across the butt) so I didn't ever wear the belt for more than 3 hours at a time.  That's not a problem with the product necessarily - probably all hip belts feel awkward.  I would mostly wear the hip belt at a time when I'd be up and walking around, cooking, etc, because it felt awkward to wear while sitting.  If I sat down in any kind of soft chair, the belt would shimmy up around my hip bones, necessitating a readjustment when I stood (not to be done in company).  The elastic side bands for getting just the right tightness were great, and also present in the Shrinkx Belly band.

I wore the hip belt starting at 1 week postpartum, for about 1-3 hours, about 5 days out of 7.  I wore it until 7 weeks postpartum (when I developed some pubic symphysis pain that my midwife & neurologist didn't think were related to the hip belt).  I wore it after my second (and last) child and my hips went from 36 inches to 34.5 inches.  I wish I knew what my pre-pregnancy hip size was, but the best test for me is the ability to fit into my favorite jeans again - and I do!  (admittedly, how much to attribute to the belt, I don't know).
summary: A little uncomfortable, but probably effective - worth it

reviewText: excellent wallet.

This is a very minimalist wallet and if it didn't have the swoosh on it and come packaged in a beautiful box with magnetic catch, it would be just another $5 wallet. That's fine though because I was looking for a thin wallet that didn't have a hundred pockets and dividers in the currency sleeve, as though I need to keep my hundreds separated from my fives. Well, this fits the bill (pun intended- note singular use of the noun) but they've taken the minimalist design a tad too far. Cards do not fit in the slots and once you have forced them in you need pliers to get them out. There are only 6 card slots but oddly when they are all filled the wallet is reluctant to close flat, and that's before you try to put anything in the hidden sections. And as far as folding money is concerned, my advice is to travel light; perhaps a couple of hundreds because much more than that and wallet is not going to fold flat. This is basically a step up from a money clip so unless you travel with maybe 4 credit (ATM, library, Moose Lodge Club, etc) cards, a couple of biz cards and a few bills you can drop the "fold" from "billfold". Overall a nice looking wallet with just average construction. Oddly, the long section of leather is split into 2 pieces. Not sure if this is a design feature or just saving cost on a larger piece of leather but creates an annoying bump where the overlap seam occurs vertically, just past the halfway point on the backside of the wallet. Did I mention the nice box...?

reviewText:
I bought one of these for a friend, and my husband bought one, as a surprise, for me - since my friend and I are closing down our Rose & Thorn Journal, I wanted something to commemorate the many years we worked together on the online 'magazine.' After much searching, this was the only piece that fit the "rose and thorn" look I wanted. There were so many "rose-colored" items, or rose-shaped jewelry, but to find a piece that had both rose and thorn, and was pretty and interesting to boot, I couldn't be happier.

It's a delicate piece but also a statement piece that isn't too feminine and cutesy - something I didn't want in a "rose" theme--so you have something that people will notice and comment on, but not something that calls too much attention to itself. It lies nice against my chest, as well. The chain isn't a good quality but for the price I didn't expect it to be, and didn't care, for I have other chains--besides, I didn't even know it would come with a chain. Though, the three times I've worn it, I've kept the chain it came with, simply because it's unobtrusive enough to disappear and let the piece shine on its own. It arrives in a blue "satin" bag, along with information on how you can "power up" the amulet - I didn't buy it for that, but I'm curious to read about it.

I'm always  hesitate to buy jewelry online, for it's difficult to tell what you truly will receive. However, this piece looked prettier than the photo shows. The crystal is clear and lovely, and the red roses tiny and well-formed. The silver "thorns" wrap around the crystal, giving it that unique look. The red teardrop adds some dimension to the entire piece.

reviewText: What eyedoctors do not want you to know is that when you break your frame, if you can find one that will fit your lenses, you can pop your lenses into the new frame yourself. I broke the frame on a pair of old glasses I wear around the house. My good glasses I save for outside because replacements would cost something like $1,000. Last time I asked, they wanted $500 per lens plus the cost of the frame but a friend got me some from overseas for only a few hundred. Anyway, I wear my old glasses around the house and managed to find this frame to fit my lenses at a fraction of the cost eyeglass sites wanted. I just popped out the clear plastic lenses and popped in my own, and I was good to go. There are sites online that tell you how to do this if you want to try it yourself. The thing to remember is the shape and size of the lens part in the frame has to be the same as the shape and size of your own lenses.

I purchased this hat in red, and a seemingly similar trapper hat in a different color from Well for my son.  Prior to purchase, I submitted a question to previous purchasers AND to the seller requesting more specific sizing information.  My question went unanswered.  (as did a previous asker).  I purchased anyhow, but will be returning it.

This Pax Trading "Child/Kid" hat will not likely fit ANY child.  It is a 59-60cm hat, which is about 23 1/2 inches.  For perspective, children's hats are usually 18-20" for 3-5 year olds, and 20-22 inches for youth through grown woman.  This hat is a grown man's size.

Aside from size, this hat, when compared to the Well hat I purchased at the same time, is lacking in many ways.  This Pax Trading hat is very thin, and is made of very poor quality faux fur.  The Well hat is thicker, and is made from a much higher grade of faux fur.  It would be much warmer.  This Pax hat also has a very short chin strap for an "adjustable" closure.  The Well hat had a much better system for adjustment, offering greater flexibility for proper fit.  The Well version also has a cinch strap at the back of the neck to adjust fit & protect from cold wind whipping into the back of the hat.  No such feature on the Pax hat.

Just received my ring today and it is so gorgeous! Words cannot describe how beautiful and shiny it is! I can't believe there is something this nice available at such a great price. I saw similar rings when we went to jewelery stores that went for at least 3.5k! I was hesitant at first to buy a ring sight unseen, but after another reviewer sent me pictures and told me that after months it was still perfect, my fiance and I went ahead and ordered it. And I'm so happy we did. Customer service at Natural Diamond is great. I ordered my ring in the wrong size and they put a hold on my order until I went to get sized at a jeweler. Word of advise, get professionally sized if you can. I tried to print a sizing guide from online and measured myself to be a size 11 when I am really a size 9. Don't worry if you don't see your size, ND store will size it for you just ask! There was a bit of a mix up in the shipping process but I still got my ring in less than a week. Even with the sizing delay. I don't think it was anyone's fault I ordered it during black Friday/cyber Monday craziness and everyone was a bit backed up. Also, don't worry about the clarity and color ratings. The ring is colorless and very shiny! The distinctions only matter under 10X magnification. To the naked eye it is perfect. Overall, great experience, will definitely order from Natural Diamond store again! Thank you Aviv for always replying back promptly to my many emails!

October 2013 Update: almost 1 year later and I was loving my ring UNTIL...a diamond fell off my ring!!!! I am so upset! It is one of the little ones in the corner. At least it wasn't the big one. You better get insurance if you buy this ring.
summary: Absolutely beautiful! (Until a diamond fell off 1 year later)

reviewText:
I love my ring! I went to a local jewelry chain to get sized and an idea of what size and shape of diamond I may like. I was discouraged by how high all of the jeweler's rings sat and how big they felt. This ring is not small, but it is not obtrusive. It sits low to your finger and glitters beautifully in any light. At a size 6 the center diamond (0.5 carat) sits plenty big for me and the round cut looks nice on my long wiry fingers. The accent diamonds and white gold help the ring shine elegantly; I've received many compliments on it. I paid for half the ring myself and am so glad to have gotten such a beautiful ring, quickly and without hassle. We paid for one day shipping (with Amazon Prime) and it arrived on time!

(Which in turn makes a noticeable bump under the corsage w/ all the knots & glue.)  Another reason why I wanted this one is because none of the pictures showed the metal attachment that so many other bracelets had... just the clear plastic plate to glue the corsage on.  Well, surprise!  It came with it.  The metal piece can be taken off fairly easily, but then you have to re-tie the ribbons to the clear plate, which takes extra time.  Lastly - & also very disappointing - is that the bracelets are very tight.  I've had comments on how thin my wrists are, so I'm not asking for extra-large here.  Just big enough where you don't think it's going to break when you put it on.  The bracelet is definitely not one-size-fits-all.  It's size small. So after all these problems, I cannot recommend this bracelet. :(

reviewText:
Whenever I decide to write a product review,here or elsewhere,I always give the thing several months of use,to make sure it'll hold up,and do what it's supposed to do(unless,of course,it's a complete pile of junk right out of the box,or is misrepresented by it's seller). In this case,I don't have to. This is the kind of tough belt you used to be able to buy anywhere,but just can't find in stores anymore. Believe me,I looked. Thick(about 1/4 inch!)beautifully finished solid leather,with big,strong snaps to hold the buckle on. Very dark brown,almost black. Exactly what I was looking for. I know this belt is going to last me 20 years.

If I have to come up with a gripe,it's that the cool black chrome looking finish on the buckle is starting to rub off,after only 2 days use,and only from rubbing up against the Formica counter tops at work,as near as I can tell. The worn spots are revealing a copper finish that's going to look pretty cool itself,once more of the black rubs off,providing that the copper doesn't wear off,to reveal what? Brass?

Anyway,it ain't about the buckle. It's about the belt.

Incidentally,even those double belt loops have come in handy. I followed the advise of some people who reviewed other Orion belts,and said to get a size larger than recommended,because these belts run short. Not so! This belt is way too long. I could cut it off,I guess,but with the thoughtfully provided extra belt loop,I just move it out to the end of the belt to keep it from flopping around.

I'm just sayin'....I think them folks are fatter than they think they are ;D

This is the original bra support! It's been around for a while and does what it promises. If you suffer with back pain because of being heavily endowed but don't want surgery this is the solution. It forces you to have good posture which takes the pressure off the back.
If you aren't necessarily top-heavy but need that perk without getting rid of a favorite bra this is the solution. It comes in great colors so you can match all kinds of bras. I highly recommend it.

Every woman needs a product like this when her bar doesn't fit exactly right. The package includes three bra strap holders in three shades to match your bra along with a cute satchel. You simply put the strap holder around your bra straps and you have amazing added lift and support. In addition, the Bralief strap holder hides the straps when wearing racer-back tanks. This saves you the investment in a pricey racer-back bra. The Bralief website shows you two easy ways of putting on your bra while wearing the strap holder both from the front and back. The Bralief is one of those great inventions that makes your life easier, saves you money, and enhances your look. Well worth it!

reviewText: The Bralief is an excellent product! I have not found a product that works better. It provides support and lift as well as creating cleavage. I always use this product when I want that extra lift and want to look thinner. I am very happy with this product and use it regularly. It is also great for taming your falling bra straps or helping to secure the straps so they don't show when you're wearing a tank top style top. I LOVE the product and would recommend it above all other similar products. There is none better!

I've been using this product for years and it is truly fantastic.  It is adjustable; so that you can use the same Bralief regardless of the look that you are seeking.  That is, you can bring your bra straps in close to your neck for a halter top or just enough to relieve the pressure from years of wearing bras in the same spot on your shoulders!

Designed by a woman for woman, this product is so comfortable yet easy to use, washable, and made in the colors of your bra.  The older you are, the more children you've nursed, the more you will love the Bralief! Don't I sound like an add??? I have to keep buying them because I have three daugthers (all but one moved out of the house years ago) who always take them.  When I see a friend who buys a new shirt and her bra strap is showing, I tell her, "you need Bralief."

Finally, I love the little silky pouch they come in...it's perfect for packing my jewelry on weekend, business trips!

Great solution for older bras or just to have a younger look. We often don't realize how much our undergarments affect the overall look of our outfits. To look really great, we need to be supported. reviewText: These only work for gerber brand onsies. I assumed they would be universal snaps. It would be nice if it were noted that they aren't universal.

this was a nifty creation and it allowed me to extend the life and wearability of my onsies. the gerber brand onsies in the first place came in the wrong size and appeared to be mislabelled. so the extenders saved them from going to the too small pile.
Was looking for extenders for the first months and received extenders for onsies size 24 months. I looked and looked and no where did it say what size they were for.

I have a few of these that were given as gifts so luckily I didn't have to buy them myself. These are great for extending your onesies as long as possible so your child can get more wear out of his or her clothes. Especially if your child has a long torso, you are using cloth diapers, or if you are trying to extend the wear of your onesies because your older child has special needs. Its hard to find 2t, 3t, and beyond sizes in onesies, especially in the US. These are great gifts for new moms, especially those who are on a budget. I have both these and Add a Size Baby Clothes Extender 10-Pack, Onesie Extender and have been using them for almost a year now. They are very durable and have held up to all the washings and dryings and everyday life. The Gerber ones are a lot shorter than the One Step Ahead brand, but the OSA brand does not fit Gerber onesies so I am obliged to use both. The Gerber ones only fit Gerber brand clothing, as previously stated in the other reviews. That is disappointing, especially since there are many brands which do not make a clothing extender, and even if there were I would not want to have to buy an extender for each and every brand. Luckily Babies R Us uses the same or similar style snap and these do fit some of our Babies R Us brand onesies as well. I think the price is great, considering how many times you can use them, how durable they are, and how hard they are to find! You can't get them in stores (or at least none of the stores where I live) and they are hard to find online too. Once in a blue moon you might see some on Ebay, but the price is never as reasonable. On Etsy there are sellers who sell handmade ones for all sorts of prices. I've seen them go for $13.99 for just one onesie extender, nothing special about it except that it was made with cutesy fabric instead of plain white. For those who need onesie extenders for multiple brands, start saving your onesies that have holes or stains in them that your child can't wear. Then use the snaps and fabric from those onesies to sew an extender of your own. That way you will have one for all the brands you use. They are SO simple and fast to make yourself, even people who aren't good at sewing can do it. You can Google "Make Your Own Onesie Extender" and lots of mom blogs have done tutorials on how to do it yourself, and many techniques ranging from super easy to more advanced. Also since you can use your own fabric you can make them to match the colors your child wears, instead of plain white. I ended up making my own at night after my daughter went to sleep. I am terrible at sewing but it was really easy so I managed it somehow! I hand-sewed them and used the fabric and snaps from old onesies. I never had to buy a thing since I already had a needle and thread around the house. Every night for about a week or two I stayed up after my daughter's bedtime and watched a couple of movies while I sewed and ended up with 10 or 12 onesie extenders that go with every brand of onesie we use. I personally don't enjoy sewing but watching movies while I did it kept it from being tedious. And my daughter's daycare teachers complimented me on the onesie extenders and some of the other parents have asked if they can pay me to make some for them!
summary: Only Fits Gerber Brand, But Does Work Well

reviewText:
I bought this along with 3 other tungsten rings so I could try all of them on and compare them side by side in person. This guy was a very close runner up to the one I chose as my wedding band. The major reason I decided against it was that the corners of the little squares were ever-so-slightly sharp, so I could feel the ridges rub against the webbing of my middle and pinky fingers. (However, that means the cuts are perfectly straight and perpendicular, which is a sign of quality in my opinion). I thought that after a few days, the slight rubbing might make my adjacent fingers dry or raw. For some guys, this wouldn't be a problem, but I work at a computer all day and my hands aren't very tough.

From most angles, the whole ring is a smooth, flat shade of grayish-silver. But when the light hits it just right, all the little grooves shine. It's not tacky or too eye-catching, and in fact it was probably designed this way, which is a nice touch for such an affordable ring.
this ring fits great, and true to size,  and is comfortable.  my husband wears it everyday and it holds up great. great ring for the price.

Quick delivery.  It's a good comfortable fit as the inside is slightly domed.  The tungsten carbide material is very hard so it will be very resistent to scratches for years to come and stay good looking.

I ordered this as an inexpensive way to verify my sizing in tungsten comfort fit bands since I couldn't try one on in the correct size at any local jewelers (in all cases they only carried one sample, the correct size had to be ordered).  The jeweler measured me at 7 1/2 but most reviews say to go 1/2 smaller with tungsten rings. I ordered 7 and it fits well. The ring stays on but was not overly tight and became fairly loose when washing with soap, a 7 1/2 would be too large.

The ring itself is decent looking and is correctly represented in the picture.  Like most tungsten rings, it is darker than than other metals like white gold, and heavier. The width is exactly 8mm, thickness from inside to out is 2.5mm, and weight is 15.2 grams. There are no markings on the inside.

The only down side to this particular ring, was that the transverse decorative slots have a almost sharp edge that tends to irritate my adjacent fingers.  I'm also not used to wearing a ring so that may be part of the issue.
summary: Good value, but might irritate adjacent fingers

We have only worn these a couple days, and I have seen other feedback for rings of this type/quality/price which referred to fading or marring of the finish over time, so I will keep this review updated should that happen.  But so far all I can say is "WOW!".
These are great rings for a great price, and I'm very happy to have matching rings again (hubby lost his first one).
The inlay really shows up nicely in the light/sunlight... and the inner surface is slightly convex which makes the rings both a bit easier to slip on and more comfortable to wear.
As to the finish, at this time I look at it and it seems very high quality on the outer metal parts and inner surface, and the inner band is possibly plexiglass, Lucite, Perspex or some other acrylic/plastic.  As we are men, doing "man stuff", we'll try and take them off when working on the car, in the garden or even when washing dishes or getting into the spa.  Don't know what these activities might do to the finish and it seems best just to take care of them, no matter how inexpensive they were.  Anyway, I seem to recall that mom always took off her wedding rings when doing dishes, too.  Actually, I think I will now order another set, for "just in case"... they were that low-cost.

I was pleasantly surprised with this ring. I have an expensive gold wedding ring, but it gets damaged VERY easily if I wear it every day. So I need the strength of tungsten. I had a simple tungsten band, but somehow it became very dull (NEVER scratched) and no amount of cleaning or buffing would fix it. I just got this one, so I can't yet speak on durability. However, I was surprised how pretty the carbon fiber part is. It has a 3D effect that you can't see in the photo, which gives a depth and movement that is very nice. Also very surprising is how comfortable this ring is. The inside edges are highly rounded (comfort fit) and it does not dig into my "webbing" at all. I have trouble with rings that have sharp edges, and this is one of the best - even more comfortable than the comfort fit rounded tungsten ring I replaced. You might need 1/2 size smaller due to this effect -- it does slide on/off much easier due to the smooth, rounded inside edge.

Awesome ring, these are so cheap I bought another one with a wooden insert from another Amazon vendor so I can rotate them out. reviewText: Best running underwear EVER.

I loved my UA Original 9" Boxerjocks and didn't think I'd ever find a better pair of underwear for working out, until I found these.  My only complaint with the originals is the silky material.  While it's good quality and very comfortable, I'm still partial to more of a cotton feel.  Unfortunately I'd never been able to find a pair of boxer briefs that had that nice soft cotton feel and still held up to the demands of athletic performance.  These did just that.  They are more expensive and very difficult to find, but if you run across a pair, you definitely won't regret buying them.
was not exactly the style I was expecting but are okay have a pr of these and they tend to ride up more than the other style

Stitching is very good! material is soft and holds its fit. I bought some adidas climalite underwear and they fell apart! under armour is a great brand and they really stand behind there product!

I love the original boxerjock, so I gave these a try.  The fabric is still "wicking" like the original, but made to feel softer to the touch like cotton.  I think the added softness makes the them feel hotter than the originals.  Also, the Touch fabric doesn't seem to stretch as much as the original fabric, and so they tend to ride-up the leg more than the originals.  I'm sticking with the original boxerjock.

I've only worn these a few times so far but I'm very, very pleased.  They don't bunch up, they don't rub, they nicely and snug in all the right areas.  They support your man parts, but don't strangle them, which was a common problem I've found in the past versions of the mostly spandex sports shorts.  I plan on buying bunches more.
summary: Great Fit, Great Feel, Great amazon price

reviewText: Very nice item, Excellent Seller

I had a Coach Signature Messenger Bag 70283 in Burgundy that fit my macbook Air 11 and iPearl mCover Hard Shell Cover Case For 11.6-inch Apple MacBook Air A1370 & A1465 - PURPLE perfectly, I loved the different compartments that made all my stuff easy to find. Despite its slim design, I wasn't very happy with the Ipearl case, the snaps broke off easily so I went on a hunt for a new cover and found this one Macally Protective Case Cover for 11-Inch MacBook Air (SlimFolio11BL). I loved it. Its twice as much as the IPearl mcover but I think its completely worth it. If you don't mind adding an extra inch to the total length of your laptop, I highly recommend it. I wrote a review on it, if you want to check it out. Unfortunately, the Macally case did not fit well in my current messenger bag. I could squeeze it in but it stretched out the sides (with the case on, the macbook is almost 13in in length and the messenger bag was 12in wide) which left no room to add anything else. The next thing to do, logically, was spend another couple of hundred dollars on a new messenger bag. Duh. :p I really like Coach bags in general. I find them to be a perfect mix of quality and style without going overboard on price and was hoping to find a similar bag to the 70283 that could accommodate the extra inch the Macally case added. I didn't want a large bag, I wanted it as compact as possible but could still carry a few books along with my laptop and found the Kyra Messenger Bag. I liked the soft, feminine, lilac color. It wasn't too ostentatious and the size was perfect. They are very similar in style. The strap is a little narrower than the 70283 but its still wide and comfortable. I do miss the double pockets in the front of the 70283, this one only has one large pocket across the front but its still functional. Overall, it has met my needs and I am really happy with it.
summary: A Great Replacement That Fits My Macally Case For Macbook Air 11

reviewText: Excellent!

The gloves fitted, well, like a glove, they have a nice feel, good grip and are nice and cool in the Australian heat of 39 deg C inside a car.

After a few weeks of wearing them, I have just noticed a loose thread, which is probably where the stitch was finished and needs to be trimmed so that it doesn't get caught on anything.

Having said that, I would purchase another pair.

The quality of these gloves is as you would expect for a company with the reputation that Dents has. The overall fit is very good on these gloves.  I purchased the medium size, and I am very pleased with the tightness of the gloves through the palm and the perfect length on the fingers. The thumb however is a tad (quarter inch, approximately) too long for me, which is odd given that I have fairly long thumbs to begin with. The over length is not terrible and the rest of the thumb fitment is great. Knuckle perforations are well placed, and the stitching is very good throughout (especially in the tips of the fingers, there is nothing worse than awkwardly overlapped stitching at the finger tips!)
I purchased the tan variety, and the colors are fairly accurately displayed from pictures here; as I expected, they are actually a bit darker and richer that the photo's show, and they do look great.
I wish that they would model the gloves on actual hands, as they do look totally different. I will try to add some photos myself, but you'll have to forgive the quality, I'm not much of a photographer (or hand model for that matter!)

Complaints:
Dents places their tags in the inside palm, and the tags are quite large (large enough that they will protrude from the opening of the gloves when worn), which ultimately forces you to cut them off. Because they're sewn into the leather at the attachment point of the thumb you won't be able to get a clean cut. The gloves are meant to be worn, so I am not concerned about a slightly ugly tag cut on the inside, but for the price its something to be mentioned.
summary: Excellent quality, and very nice fit.
